        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 6:50PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 649 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking several clusters of
strengthening thunderstorms in teh advisory area, with the strongest
cell located 7 miles southeast of Fyffe, or 7 miles southwest of
Fort Payne. All storms were moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40-50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Payne, Geraldine, Lakeview, Dog Town, Collbran, Guest, Little
River Canyon NP, Skirum, Lebanon, and Pine Ridge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
northeastern Alabama.</instruction>
